# HTML & CSS Notes (Organized)

## Typography Properties
1. font-family → Text ka font set karne ke liye. (Google Fonts se import kar sakte ho, jaise: Poppins)
2. font-style → italic / normal set karne ke liye.
3. font-weight → boldness control karta hai (100–900).
4. text-decoration → underline, overline, line-through add karne ke liye.
5. line-height → do lines ke beech ki vertical spacing.
6. text-transform → text ko UPPERCASE, lowercase, ya Capitalize me change karne ke liye.

---

## Overflow Handling
1. overflow: hidden; → extra content chhup jata hai.
2. overflow: scroll; → hamesha scrollbar show hota hai.
3. overflow-x / overflow-y → sirf horizontal ya vertical overflow control.
   - Example: overflow: hidden auto; (x hidden, y auto-scroll).
4. white-space: nowrap; → content ek hi line me force hoga.
5. text-overflow: ellipsis; → text cut hoke "..." show karega.

---

## CSS Units
1. px → fixed pixel size.
2. vw → viewport width ka percentage.
3. vh → viewport height ka percentage.
4. em → parent element ke font-size ke relative (2em = double size).
5. rem → root element ke font-size ke relative.
6. vmin → viewport ki min(width, height).
7. vmax → viewport ki max(width, height).

---

## Shadows & Outline
Box Shadow Syntax:
box-shadow: h-offset v-offset blur spread color inset;

- h-offset = left-right move
- v-offset = up-down move
- blur = kitna blur hoga
- spread = size expand/shrink
- color = shadow ka rang
- inset = andar shadow lagta hai

Outline Syntax:
outline: width style color;

- width = outline ki thickness
- style = solid, dotted, dashed
- color = outline ka color

---

## Positioning in CSS
1. static → Default position.
2. relative → element apni original jagah ke relative move hota hai.
3. absolute → nearest positioned ancestor ke relative place hota hai.
4. fixed → viewport ke respect me fixed hota hai (scroll karne par bhi same jagah).
5. sticky → ek jagah chipak jata hai jab tak scroll hota hai.

Extra:
- top, bottom, left, right → positioning ke liye.
- z-index → stacking order control karta hai. Sirf positioned elements (relative/absolute/fixed/sticky) pe kaam karta hai.

