## CSS Variables
:root {
  --main-color: blue;
  --padding: 10px;
}
.box {
  color: var(--main-color);
  padding: var(--padding);
}

---

## Media Queries
Responsive design ke liye use hota hai.

Syntax:
@media not/only mediatype and (condition) {
  /* CSS Code */
}

Examples:
@media only screen and (max-width: 455px) {
  body { background-color: blue; }
  .box { flex-direction: column; }
}

@media screen and (orientation: landscape) {
  body { background-color: green; }
}

---

## Display Properties
1. display: flex; → elements ko row/column me arrange karne ke liye.
2. display: grid; → 2D layout ke liye.
   Example:
   grid-template-columns: 120px 100px;

3. display: inline-block;
   - Element line me rahta hai (inline ki tarah).
   - Width/height set kar sakte ho (block ki tarah).
   - Use case: chhoti boxes ko side-by-side rakhna.

